<br>
What happens is a guide comes along - gets your petition from the queue (they are in it chronologically, oldest at top)  <br>
<br>
He sends a tell to whomever submitted it: <br>
“Hello, I am Guide Soandso, how can I be of service?”<br>
<br>
If your offline, he has the option of either saving it or deleting it.  If he saves it, he can annotate it with what ever extra action is required, and flag it for a Senior Guide or a Verant GM to handle.<br>
<br>
When a Sr. Guide or a GM get it, they can also delete if your not online.  Just to keep a nice clean petition queue.<br>
<br>
When you log, your petition is never automatically deleted, except by server-reset.  It takes interaction on the CS side to kill a petition that you don’t delete yourself.<br>
<br>
